'''Charlie Noble''' is the [[smoke stack]] on a ship's [[Galley (kitchen)|galley]].
Around 1850, a British [[Merchant Navy (United Kingdom)|merchant service]] captain, Charles Noble, upon discovering that the stack of his ship's galley was made of [[copper]], ordered that it be kept bright. From then onwards the ship's crew then started referring to the galley smokestack as the "'''Charlie Noble'''".
