[[File:PS mapo 2015.png|thumb|400x400px|Cities in the world with Pasporta Servo hosts as of 2015]]
{{Esperanto sidebar |expanded=Services}}
The '''Pasporta Servo''' ({{lang-en|'''Passport Service'''}}) is a  [[hospitality service]] for [[Esperanto]] speakers. It is maintained by the [[World Esperanto Youth Organization]] (TEJO), which publishes an annual online and print directory of people within the [[Esperanto culture]] who are willing to host other Esperanto speakers in their [[residence]]s for free for up to 3 nights. The platform is a [[gift economy]]; hosts are not allowed to charge for [[lodging]].

Free lodging via Pasporta Servo is one of the benefits of learning [[Esperanto]].<ref>{{cite news | title=One of the Perks of Speaking Esperanto? Free Lodging Around the World | url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/one-of-the-perks-of-speaking-esperanto-free-lodging-around-the-world-1415754748 | last=Wells | first=Charlie | work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] | date=11 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=The Joy of Esperanto | url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/the-joy-of-esperanto | last=SCHOR | first=ESTHER | work=[[The Daily Beast]] | date=30 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Esperanto Is Not Dead: Can The Universal Language Make A Comeback? | url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2015/06/13/413968033/esperanto-is-not-dead-can-the-universal-language-make-a-comeback | last=SIEG | first=STINA | work=[[NPR]] | date=13 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Feliĉa Ferioj! Toasting the Holidays in Esperanto | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/12/21/nyregion/esperanto-nyc.html | last=KILGANNON | first=COREY | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=21 December 2017}}</ref> Guests using the service are encouraged to speak only Esperanto with their hosts.

==History==
In 1966, psychologist [[Rubén Feldman González]] started the ''Programo Pasporto'', a hospitality service for Esperanto speakers, in [[Argentina]]. In 1974, under the guidance of [[Jeanne-Marie Cash]] in [[France]], the Pasporta Servo directory in its current form was first published, listing 40 hosts. Both founders are still hosts in the Pasporta Servo.

In August 2008, TEJO launched Pasporta Servo 2.0, an online version of the service.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.liberafolio.org/arkivo/www.liberafolio.org/2008/tejokomitato2008/ | title=TEJO reformas Pasportan Servon | work=[[Libera Folio]] | date=1 August 2008}}</ref>

